[Differential intellectual progress](http://wiki.lesswrong.com/wiki/Differential_intellectual_progress#Risk-reducing_Progress%0A) on LW wiki has a bit on this:

> One way by which AGIs might grow rapidly more powerful is by taking
> over poorly-protected computers on the Internet. Hardening computers
> and networks against such attacks would help reduce this risk.

Even without considering greater-than-human intelligences, poor computer security can
still lead to harm to individuals or organizations through information leaks and
harm to computer systems.

